{NORTH has a normal 1\S opening bid, 14 points and five trumps.

SOUTH has good 4-card support and 7 points, so she raises to 2\S. 

NORTH passes, knowing he is not missing a game contract. SOUTH can have a maximum of 10 points, which would 
only reach 24 points when added to his 14.}

