{With a 5-card \S suit and 16 points SOUTH should open 1\S.

NORTH has 11 points and four \Ss. So even though he has a balanced hand, 
he jumps to 3\S, a Limit Raise.

SOUTH adds: her 16 plus NORTH's 11/12 equals a game, 4\S.}

