[Student "S"]
{NORTH has the type of 5-card Major hand that many players would open 1NT. 
He has 17 points with most of them OUTSIDE the Major suit. But, many others 
would disagree so for this Deal NORTH will open 1\S.

SOUTH has 11 points and excellent (is that strong enough?) \S support. 
So she naturally makes a Limit Raise of 3\S.

NORTH adds the points and ignores the fact that his \S suit is Jack high. 
He bids 4\S.}

